Description:
Hi, I found a bug in Verilator 5.001 (Compiled commit: ed93a111c285ce36e185ed45a45cf9e0d33c9b6a).
This is the minimal testcase I've managed to write:
module t (
   input clk
 );
   typedef struct packed {
        logic signed [63:0] b;
    } a_t;

    a_t a_r, a_n;
    logic signed [63:0] b;
    logic res;

    assign b = a_r.b;

    always_comb begin
        a_n = a_r;
        res = '0;
        if (b inside {1, 2}) begin
            res = 1'b1;
        end
    end

    always_ff @(posedge clk ) begin
       a_r <= a_n;
    end    

endmodule
The following internal error is produced:
%Error: Internal Error: t_peephole_inside.sv:18:26: ../V3DfgPeephole.cpp:843: Mismatched RHS width
   18 |         if (b inside {1, 2}) begin
      |                          ^
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html for more assistance.
